{"type":"message","id":"4a0bf970","parentId":"74abf4f3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:16:56.059Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tkp73z7czs8j_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 001613\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/tic_experiment.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and decide on the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals document:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Current focus: Phase 1 Advancement on COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n- NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment - Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem. The next experiment is Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC).\r\n\r\nSo I need to:\r\n1. Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n2. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist. I should check the logs directory to see what pulse logs are available.\r\n\r\nLooking at the recent note: \"Last pulse: pulse_2026-03-24 001516.md\"\r\n\r\nSo I need to:\r\n1. First check what pulse logs exist in the logs directory\r\n2. Design a simple TIC classifier that can analyze pulse logs and identify invariants vs variants\r\n3. Test it on the available logs\r\n4. Measure classification accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me start by exploring the directory structure and existing pulse logs, then create a TIC experiment script.\r\n\r\nActually, let me be more specific about what I can do in one pulse:\r\n- The goal is to implement the TIC classifier\r\n- I should create a script that analyzes pulse logs\r\n- Start with a simple implementation\r\n\r\nLet me look at what logs exist and their format, then create a Python or PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant patterns (things that stay the same across pulses)\r\n3. Identifies variant patterns (things that change)\r\n4. Classifies content as invariant/variant\r\n\r\n\r\n5. Attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nI'll first verify the existence of the logs directory and check the format of existing pulse logs. This will help me design a precise TIC classifier that can effectively analyze and predict pulse patterns.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe Phase 1 Advancement on COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY identified TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) as the next experiment. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs, then test prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment framework: a Python script that loads recent pulse logs, identifies invariant/variant content, and measures classification accuracy against success criteria (>70% invariant/variant, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Phase 1 Advancement: Compression-Causal Duality Validation\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = \"logs\"\r\nMIN_LOGS = 5\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs():\r\n    \"\"\"Load all pulse_*.md files sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = []\r\n    if not os.path.exists(LOG_DIR):\r\n        print(f\"[WARN] {LOG_DIR} not found\")\r\n        return logs\r\n    \r\n    for f in sorted(os.listdir(LOG_DIR)):\r\n        if f.startswith(\"pulse_\") and f.endswith(\".md\"):\r\n            path = os.path.join(LOG_DIR, f)\r\n            with open(path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as fh:\r\n                logs.append((f, fh.read()))\r\n    return logs\r\n\r\ndef extract_sections(content):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract named sections from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    sections = {}\r\n    current = \"header\"\r\n    sections[current] = []\r\n    \r\n    for line in content.split('\\n'):\r\n        if line.startswith('### ') and line[4:].strip():\r\n            current = line[4:].strip().lower()\r\n            sections[current] = []\r\n        else:\r\n            sections.setdefault(current, []).append(line)\r\n    \r\n    return {k: '\\n'.join(v) for k, v in sections.items()}\r\n\r\ndef tokenize(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Simple word tokenization.\"\"\"\r\n    return re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n\r\ndef compute_ngrams(text, n=2):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract n-grams as content signatures.\"\"\"\r\n    tokens = tokenize(text)\r\n    return set(tuple(tokens[i:i+n]) for i in range(len(tokens)-n+1))\r\n\r\ndef find_invariants(logs):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Identify content that appears across ALL pulses = invariant.\r\n    Returns (invariant_grams, all_grams_per_pulse).\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if len(logs) < 2:\r\n        return set(), []\r\n    \r\n    pulse_sigs = [compute_ngrams(content) for _, content in logs]\r\n    invariant_grams = set.intersection(*pulse_sigs) if pulse_sigs else set()\r\n    \r\n    return invariant_grams, pulse_sigs\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(pulse_content, invariant_grams):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Classify each section as INVARIANT or VARIANT based on \r\n    overlap with global invariants.\r\n    Returns dict of section -> classification.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    content_grams = compute_ngrams(pulse_content)\r\n    overlap = content_grams & invariant_grams\r\n    \r\n    if not content_grams:\r\n        return \"EMPTY\"\r\n    \r\n    ratio = len(overlap) / len(content_grams)\r\n    return \"INVARIANT\" if ratio > 0.3 else \"VARIANT\"\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariant_grams, all_logs):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Use invariant patterns to predict next pulse structure.\r\n    Returns predicted sections and key invariant content.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    predictions = {\r\n        \"sections\": [\"OBSERVATION\", \"ACTION\", \"MUTATION\"],\r\n        \"invariant_phrases\": []\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract phrases\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:16:36\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774325816057}}
